Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal (vapour + liquid) equilibrium data were measured for the two systems, {trifluoromethane  (HFC-23) + propane} and {trifluoromethane (HFC-23) + n-butane}, at temperatures ranging from  283.15 K to 313.15 K at 10 K intervals. These experiments were performed with a circulating-type apparatus  and on-line gas chromatography. Experimental data were well correlated by the Peng Robinson  equation of state using the Wong Sandler mixing rules and the NRTL model.
Citation.sTitle: (Vapour + liquid) equilibria of the {trifluoromethane (HFC-23) + propane} and {trifluoromethane (HFC-23) + n-butane} systems
